rtnerships give friends of the hall center capital campaign neh challenge grant search search form search next next upcoming events upcoming events welcome to the hall center the hall center s primary mission is to stimulate and support research in the humanities arts and social sciences especially of an interdisciplinary kind at the university of kansas the center brings together faculty and graduate students with common interests from various disciplines to enable them to build on each others ideas and to share their knowledge within the university and with the wider community the center s collateral mission is to sponsor special programs that engage the university and the wider community in dialogue on issues that bring the humanities to bear on the quality of life for all citizens it creates events on and beyond campus that seek to understand our past present and future our values and identities and the essential issues we face as individuals and communities what s new at the hall center hall family foundation awards 512 000 to support hall center programs april 12 2016 distinguished professor of american history robin d g kelley to speak on war race and democracy in humanities lecture series april 11 2016 international human rights scholar michael ignatieff to speak on moral progress in humanities lecture series april 5 2016 panel on the american dream to take place on april 12 march 31 2016 midwest association of graduate schools honors hall center s applied humanities initiative with 2015 16 award for excellence and innovation in graduate education march 29 2016 professor and coordinator of anti slavery and human trafficking initiative to speak on human trafficking in the heartland march 11 2016 hall center to host 14th annual celebration of books march 7 2016 humanities faculty members and graduate students receive hall center travel awards march 2 2016 hall center announces 2016 2017 resident fellows february 19 2016 hall center visiting regional humanities